 NGOZI OKORIE ONE of former Governor Rochas Okorocha’s aides, arraigned before a Magistrate’s Court in Owerri Imo State, slumped inside the court room on Monday. This happened just before the court granted the accused persons N5million bail each. They are to meet the bail conditons before their release. The aide, Darlington Ibekwe, is being arraigned, alongside 13 others, on a six-count charge, bordering on disturbance of the security of the state and destruction of government seal at Royal Spring Palm Estate, Owerri, among others. Police Prosecutor, Omo-Osagie M. A. had informed the court that Okorocha’s other aides – Lasbery Okaforanyanwu, Ijeoma Igboanusi – including Uche Nwosu and Uzoma Anwuka, were at large. Ibekwe was accused of publishing a defamatory matter on social media with intent to injure the reputation of the state government and the person of Governor Hope Uzodimma by exposing to hatred, contempt, ridicule and damage his reputation. Olu Chizoba was also accused of unlawful possession of a double barrel pump action gun without licence, among other counts read out against the aides. After the plea for bail, before Magistrate B. U. Adikaibe, returned to the courtroom for her ruling, Ibekwe had slumped inside the court room. He was revived by his colleagues. Those who were arraigned were Ibekwe, Obasi Goodluck, Nwaiwu Ndubuisi, Median Ijeoma, Obor Victor, Ucheka Claudin, Sunday Chisom and Ekpendu Peace. Others included Nev F. Raphael, Basil Mba, Steve Asimobi, Ebere Nwokeji, Eberendu Chimechifulam and Olu Chizoba. 